How I refresh my knotless braids | 🧖🏽‍♀️🫧

One thing about me - I’m going to get my money’s worth. These are my go-to steps for maintaining fresh looking braids for as long as possible.

I typically reach for a water based hair rinse to remove build up and reduce dandruff from my scalp. Shampoo works great as well, just make sure you dilute it with water. The most important step when cleansing your scalp and roots is to be as *gentle* as possible. 
 
I sit under a hooded dryer using cool heat for at least 15-20 minutes but the longer the better. This ensures my roots dry as flat as possible. If you don’t have a hooded dryer, a blow dryer works great too! 

I’ve linked all the products on my Amazon storefront. 💕

#protectivestyles #bohotknotlessbraids #knotlessbraids #knotlessboxbraids #washday #washbraids #braidstyles #naturalhair #haircaretips #dmvblogger

Come with me to @peachystudio to get AI-powered preventative Botox! 💉✨

I’ll be 34 this month and while I don’t have many issues with wrinkles, I’m all for preventive treatment. @peachystudio just opened a brand new location in Navy Yard, DC and it’s definitely worth the visit. This was my first time ever getting Botox and the experience couldn’t have been better.

What I love most is that they offer a transparent flat rate, so no matter the number of units you need, the price is always $425.

They were generous enough to give me a discount code. Use code 4j9uo0 when scheduling your appointment online to save an extra $50 off your first wrinkle relaxer treatment!

#peachystudio #navyyarddc #prevenativebotox #affordablebotox # sponsored
